# CODEOWNERS — TASK-2297 fleet CI enforcement.
#
# Every path below is on the fleet's protected-path list: a change here can
# redefine what a "required check" tests, or silently no-op it, without the
# PR looking suspicious. The org ruleset's "Require review from Code Owners"
# toggle means a PR touching any of these paths cannot merge without an
# approving review from the listed owner — deliberately the HUMAN account,
# never hydrata-ci-bot. See docs/fleet-enforcement/OPERATOR-CHECKLIST.md in
# the Hydrata/deploy repo for the full governance bundle.
#
# NO branch-wide minimum-approval count is set anywhere in the ruleset — a
# green PR touching NONE of the paths below needs zero human approvals and
# auto-merges. Only PRs touching a path below require the human.
